---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Mikael Ristmets.">
  <article class="container">
    <header class="head">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>A short note from <em>Mikael</em>.</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Mina usun, et arhitektuur pole üksnes ruumikujundamise tööriist,
        vaid ka ühiskonna, misläbi on võimalik luua paremat elu kõigile.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>
          Architecture is not just something we use to design the space
          around us, but something that also shapes society, which allows
          for the creation of better lives for everyone.
        </em>
      </p>

      <h2>About this site</h2>
      <p>
        This site is an ongoing archive of work: architecture, furniture,
        installations, photography, video, drawings, music, and coffee.
        The index lists everything newest-first. Each section is a
        filtered slice of the same archive.
      </p>

      <h2>Colophon</h2>
      <p>
        Set in <em>Iowan Old Style</em> (with Palatino, Charter and Georgia
        as fallbacks). Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>
        and statically rendered. All entries live as Markdown files next
        to their images in this repository.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .head {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-8);
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--fs-2xl);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: var(--lh-tight);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  h1 em { font-style: italic; }
</style>
